Vyse Ave., adjoining and at the S.E. corner of East 176th Street. The 2-story center house bears No. 1864. Also shown (left) is the elevated structure of the I.R.T. White Plains Road subway line running north on Boston Road. The latest (1937) map of the borough issued by the Geographical Map Co. shows the site to be occupied as a playground.

July 31, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.
